# ADR draft: add `__HOSTNAME__` to sources.yaml

**Status:** draft — maintainer review pending.
**Generated by:** `plugins/agentify/lib/mkt_self_improve_postflight.sh` (FR-7).
**Generated at:** `__GENERATED_AT__`.

## Context

A `/mkt-self-improve` audit ran on `__AUDIT_DATE__` and surfaced a trend backed by content from `__URL__` — a hostname (`__HOSTNAME__`) not yet tracked in `plugins/agentify/conventions/sources.yaml` or referenced from `plugins/agentify/context/*.md`.

Per PRD 0003 FR-7, audits citing new domains in their `## Trend findings` section must produce a paired draft ADR proposing the source for the curated list. The audit otherwise refuses to land. This closes the discovery loop: discoveries trigger review-ready additions to the authority list, so future audits' substantive-fetch gate (FR-3, FR-5) can draw on the new source.

## Trend quote

> __TREND_QUOTE__

## Recommendation

Add the following entry to `plugins/agentify/conventions/sources.yaml` under `sources:` after maintainer review:

```yaml
- id: __RECOMMENDED_ID__
  driver: html-index  # OR html / rss / sitemap / github-readme / github-releases — pick during review
  url: __URL__
  cadence_hint: weekly  # tune during review
  authority_weight: __RECOMMENDED_AUTHORITY_WEIGHT__  # 1-5; >=4 unlocks auto-open ADR threshold
  applicability_tags: []  # populate during review
```

## Decision

_Maintainer fills in on accept/reject:_

- [ ] **Accept** — move this draft to `decisions/<NNNN>-add-source-__RECOMMENDED_ID__.md`, update `sources.yaml`, run `practice_track fetch __RECOMMENDED_ID__` once to seed baseline.
- [ ] **Reject** — hype-train / low signal / already covered by an existing source. Delete this draft; the next audit will re-surface it if the trend recurs.
- [ ] **Defer** — interesting but not yet authoritative enough. Keep this draft in place; revisit next quarter.

## Consequences

If accepted: `__HOSTNAME__` joins the curated authority list. Future `/mkt-self-improve` Phase 8 runs fetch from it; future audits can cite it without triggering FR-7 again. FR-3's dynamic minimum scales by +1.

If rejected: the trend is still visible in the audit (`audits/__AUDIT_ID__.md` Trend findings section retains the citation). Reviewers can revisit later.

